WEBVTT

00:00:03.790 --> 00:00:12.789
They said, you've got to go to Alaska, one of the greatest assignments you can be provided from the branch.

00:00:12.789 --> 00:00:17.789
And then he popped up with the question, is this have you ever thought of going to Alaska?

00:00:17.789 --> 00:00:22.789
And we said, well, should we?

00:00:22.789 --> 00:00:27.789
We definitely had to pray about it, scripturally look up some things.

00:00:27.789 --> 00:00:31.789
And we talked to two couples that we knew that had served in Alaska.

00:00:31.789 --> 00:00:36.789
You're assigned to the people, and if you focus on that, then you'll find joy in your assignment no matter where it is.

00:00:36.789 --> 00:00:43.789
I do also like the spirit of Isaiah, where Jehovah asked, who shall I send, without hesitation.

00:00:43.789 --> 00:00:49.789
Isaiah pipes up, here I am, send me, he was just willing to be sent.

00:00:49.789 --> 00:00:56.789
And then there was logistics of figuring out how to simplify and how to actually get up there.

00:00:56.789 --> 00:01:01.789
It definitely takes courage to take an assignment where you're out of your comfort zone.

00:01:01.789 --> 00:01:09.790
We might have needed some courage for the assignment that we took, but we were so impressed with the courage that the other brothers demonstrated.

00:01:09.790 --> 00:01:17.790
There were a total 16 different special pioneers that were assigned, and six of them had never experienced a winter.

00:01:17.790 --> 00:01:23.790
And they're being sent into the harshest of climates, the harshest of winters in northern Alaska.

00:01:23.790 --> 00:01:33.790
When we saw these young men, without hesitation, going to very unique places out of their comfort zone, it inspired us.

00:01:33.790 --> 00:01:42.790
And it wasn't just a harsh climate, but it was darkness, no congregations, none of their friends, none of the family there.

00:01:43.790 --> 00:01:56.790
They would get a taxi cab, drive them to the furthest part of their territory for that particular day, drop them off, and then they would work from that location back to their hotel.

00:01:56.790 --> 00:02:02.790
I would say one of the blessings that we enjoyed was seeing how Jehovah opened up the language group.

